Vernon D. YELTON v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 4061. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. March 15, 1950. W. A. Sutherland, Las Cruces, New Mexico, for appellant. Everett M. Grantham, United States Attorney, and Albert H. Clancy, Assistant United States Attorney, Albuquerque, New Mexico, for appellee.

Before PHILLIPS, Chief Judge, and BRATTON, HUXMAN, MURRAH and PICKETT, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Docketed and dismissed, on motion of appellee, for failure to prosecute.
